---
const points = [
    {
        title: "Works with every GLP-1",
        copy: "Zepbound, Mounjaro, Ozempic, Wegovy, Rybelsus, compounded options. Shots or pills, weekly or daily, Glu adapts to each protocol.",
    },
    {
        title: "Built for the whole arc",
        copy: "Ramp-up, plateaus, dose changes, maintenance, and life after treatment. The app is designed for years, not weeks.",
    },
    {
        title: "Data in your control",
        copy: "Logs stay under your control. Delete the account and everything in it, anytime, from inside the app or the website.",
    },
    {
        title: "Calm, not clinical pressure",
        copy: "No streaks to lose, no guilt mechanics. Just a clear picture of where you are and gentle reminders for what is next.",
    },
];
---

<section id="trust" class="bg-surface-raised px-6 py-28 sm:px-10 sm:py-36" aria-label="Trust">
    <div
        class="mx-auto grid w-full max-w-screen-xl gap-16 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_1fr] lg:gap-24"
    >
        <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-28 lg:self-start">
            <h2
                data-reveal
                class="max-w-xl font-display text-[clamp(2rem,4.5vw,3.4rem)] font-bold leading-[1.06] tracking-[-0.025em] text-ink"
            >
                Sensitive by nature. Treated that way.
            </h2>
            <p
                data-reveal
                style="--reveal-delay: 0.1s"
                class="mt-6 max-w-md text-base leading-relaxed text-ink-soft sm:text-lg"
            >
                A weight and medication journal is some of the most personal
                data there is. Glu is built so it stays yours.
            </p>
            <a
                data-reveal
                style="--reveal-delay: 0.18s"
                href="/privacy"
                class="mt-8 inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm font-semibold text-brand transition-colors hover:text-brand-deep"
            >
                Read the privacy policy
                <svg
                    class="h-4 w-4"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                >
                    <path d="M5 12h14"></path>
                    <path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"></path>
                </svg>
            </a>
        </div>

        <ul class="flex flex-col">
            {
                points.map((point, index) => (
                    <li
                        data-reveal
                        style={`--reveal-delay: ${index * 0.08}s`}
                        class="border-t border-slate-200 py-9 first:border-t-0 first:pt-0 last:pb-0"
                    >
                        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold tracking-[-0.01em] text-ink">
                            {point.title}
                        </h3>
                        <p class="mt-3 max-w-lg text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                            {point.copy}
                        </p>
                    </li>
                ))
            }
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="bg-surface px-6 pb-28 sm:px-10 sm:pb-36" aria-label="Expert guidance">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-screen-xl">
        <div
            data-reveal
            class="rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-[0_30px_70px_-50px_rgba(15,23,42,0.3)] sm:p-10"
        >
            <div class="max-w-3xl">
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-faint">
                    Expert Guidance
                </p>
                <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-[clamp(1.8rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold leading-[1.08] tracking-[-0.025em] text-ink">
                    What established guidance says about GLP&#8209;1 treatment
                </h2>
                <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-base leading-relaxed text-ink-soft sm:text-lg">
                    Glu does not provide medical advice, but it is designed around the kind of monitoring and follow-up that established clinical guidance treats as important.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-10 grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-2">
                <article class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-200 bg-surface-raised p-6">
                    <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold leading-[1.14] tracking-[-0.015em] text-ink">
                        Ongoing monitoring matters
                    </h3>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft sm:text-base">
                        The Endocrine Society recommends assessing the efficacy and safety of weight-loss medications at least monthly for the first 3 months, then at least every 3 months.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-ink-faint">
                        Source:
                        <a
                            href="https://www.endocrine.org/clinical-practice-guidelines/pharmacological-management-of-obesity"
                            class="text-ink underline decoration-slate-300 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-slate-900"
                        >
                            Endocrine Society Clinical Practice Guideline
                        </a>
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-200 bg-surface-raised p-6">
                    <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold leading-[1.14] tracking-[-0.015em] text-ink">
                        Product quality and safety matter too
                    </h3>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft sm:text-base">
                        The American Diabetes Association recommends against non-FDA-approved compounded GLP-1 products because of uncertainty about their content, safety, quality, and effectiveness.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-ink-faint">
                        Source:
                        <a
                            href="https://diabetes.org/newsroom/press-releases/american-diabetes-association-announces-statement-compounded-incretin"
                            class="text-ink underline decoration-slate-300 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-slate-900"
                        >
                            American Diabetes Association
                        </a>
                    </p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
